page.title: 10Ecology
page.content: There is plenty of wild life in our area.There are some foxes in it.Although they aren't seen very much they leave footprints and live in earths.There are also badgers.They are grey on their faces.A sett is dug in the ground.A badgers sett can be 4-5 metres deep.They have sharp teeth and claws.It eats rabbits.Rabbits are quick on their feet and they also live in burrows.There are lots of wild plants in the fields and hedges.The daisy is one of our most common flowers we have in our fields.It is about 6 to 7 cm's high with white petals and yellow in the middle.
